						               													<description>The game consists of two ivory colored 'Soccer dice'. One is printed with red text, and the other is printed with green text.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The dice with red text is used for 'playing' the game, and its six faces are marked:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Pass&amp;#10;    Dribble&amp;#10;    Off side&amp;#10;    Hand Ball&amp;#10;    Shoot&amp;#10;    Shoot&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The dice with green text is used for 'shooting' at goal and its faces are marked:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Saved&amp;#10;    Re-Bound&amp;#10;    Over Bar&amp;#10;    Wide&amp;#10;    Goal &amp;#10;    Goal&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player whose turn it is rolls the first dice.  If they roll a 'pass', or 'dribble', the dice is rolled again.  If they roll a 'shoot', the second dice is rolled to determine the result.  If they roll a 'Hand Ball', or 'Off Side', play passes to the other player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When rolling the second dice, a 'Re-Bound' gives the player another shot at goal.  Otherwise play passes to the other player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Similar to Socca Dice, albeit with different die faces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
